      "version": 6,
      "versionNonce": 1837219866,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781360877818,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "# Common Rate Limiters and Their Algorithms\n\n| System / Service | Algorithm(s) Used | Notes |\n|------------------|------------------|-------|\n| NGINX | Leaky Bucket | `limit_req` module smooths traffic and prevents bursts from reaching backend services. |\n| Kong API Gateway | Fixed Window, Sliding Window, Token Bucket | Depends on plugin and configuration. Often backed by Redis. |\n| HAProxy | Sliding Counters / Token-Bucket-like | Uses stick tables to track request rates. |\n| Redis-based Custom Rate Limiter | Fixed Window (`INCR` + `EXPIRE`), Sliding Window, Token Bucket | Most common custom implementation in interviews and startups. |\n| Cloudflare | Token Bucket + Distributed Counters | Designed for globally distributed edge networks. |\n| AWS API Gateway | Token Bucket | Supports burst capacity and steady-state request limits. |\n| Google Cloud APIs | Token Bucket / Quota Systems | Combines quotas with burst handling. |\n| Apache APISIX | Fixed Window, Leaky Bucket, Token Bucket | Multiple rate-limiting plugins available. |\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "# Common Rate Limiters and Their Algorithms\n\n| System / Service | Algorithm(s) Used | Notes |\n|------------------|------------------|-------|\n| NGINX | Leaky Bucket | `limit_req` module smooths traffic and prevents bursts from reaching backend services. |\n| Kong API Gateway | Fixed Window, Sliding Window, Token Bucket | Depends on plugin and configuration. Often backed by Redis. |\n| HAProxy | Sliding Counters / Token-Bucket-like | Uses stick tables to track request rates. |\n| Redis-based Custom Rate Limiter | Fixed Window (`INCR` + `EXPIRE`), Sliding Window, Token Bucket | Most common custom implementation in interviews and startups. |\n| Cloudflare | Token Bucket + Distributed Counters | Designed for globally distributed edge networks. |\n| AWS API Gateway | Token Bucket | Supports burst capacity and steady-state request limits. |\n| Google Cloud APIs | Token Bucket / Quota Systems | Combines quotas with burst handling. |\n| Apache APISIX | Fixed Window, Leaky Bucket, Token Bucket | Multiple rate-limiting plugins available. |\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "asqAV_xTXKxUtsd2OmgLA",
      "type": "text",
